<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-692-111  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 692 111.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  Dec 3 1990* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>SCT plans plain-English query capability. (Systems and ComputerTechnology Corp. plans natural language queries for Bannersoftware series)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Buckler, Grant.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   SCT Corp. (Products).andO;Product:   IntelliQuest (Computer program) (Product development).andO;Topic:     Applications ProgrammingEnhancementsStructured Query LanguageAdd-In/On Software.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>SCT PLANS PLAIN-ENGLISH QUERY CAPABILITY 12/03/90 MALVERN, PENNSYLVANIA,U.S.A., 1990 DEC 3 (NB) -- Systems andamp; Computer Technology has unveiled plansto add an English-language query capability to its Banner Series ofapplications software products for higher education and local government.andO;Eric Haskell, senior vice-president of SCT, told Newsbytes the IntelliQuestadd-on product will be available within a year at a price yet to be decided.andM;Built on reasoning-based technology licensed from Natural Language Inc.,andO;IntelliQuest will translate plain-English inquiries into Structured QueryLanguage (SQL), Haskell said.andP;  It will display the resulting SQL query so theuser can see how the question has been translated.andM;Users can &quot;teach&quot; the software their own definitions, Haskell added.andP;  Forinstance, to query a database containing student scores on intelligencetests, one might tell the software that the word smart refers to anyone withan IQ over 130.andP;  Asking &quot;Who is smart?&quot; would then retrieve records for allstudents with IQ scores over 130.andM;The Banner software works with Oracle, the database software from theCalifornia company of the same name, and will work on any computer Oraclesupports, Haskell said.andM;IntelliQuest works with all five systems in SCT's Banner product line:Student; Finance; Financial Aid; Alumni/Development; and Human Resources.andM;(Grant Buckler/19901130/Press Contact: Eric Haskell, SCT, 215-640-5175)</TEXT></DOC>